HEADWORD: Thurible
<hw>Thu"ri*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>thuribulum</ets>, <ets>turibulum</ets>, from <ets>thus</ets>,
<ets>thuris</ets>, or better <ets>tus</ets>, <ets>turis</ets>,
frankincense, fr. Gr. <?/ a sacrifice, an offering, from <?/ to
sacrifice.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A censer of metal, for
burning incense, having various forms, held in the hand or suspended by
chains; -- used especially at mass, vespers, and other solemn
services.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

